# Git — no implicit merge

- **Never** merge branches (`git merge`, PR merge, squash merge) unless the user **explicitly** asks.
- **Never** push to `main` / `master` unless the user **explicitly** asks.
- Pushing the **current feature branch** is OK when asked; default is push only, no merge.
- If deploy needs `main`, tell the user and wait for approval — do not merge "to help."
